    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      141.02,
      710.33,
      457.42,
      737.21
    ],
    "text": "Public Awareness on Online Fraud during the Festive Season",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT",
      "Vijaya"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      751.79,
      526.34,
      792.67
    ],
    "text": "During the Sinhala and Hindu New Year festive period, the public increasingly relies on the internet for various needs, including purchasing goods and making payments. During this time, there is a rising trend of criminal activities such as financial fraud and data theft carried",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      31.91,
      526.25,
      58.99
    ],
    "text": "out through online platforms, with offenders using various deceptive methods to unlawfully obtain money and sensitive personal information.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      73.57,
      526.32,
      114.45
    ],
    "text": "Information received by Police Stations and the Criminal Investigation Department in recent years indicates that certain individuals engage in such fraudulent activities due to financial hardship and the pursuit of quick financial gain.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      129.01,
      526.42,
      197.49
    ],
    "text": "It has been identified that online scams are commonly carried out through methods such as fraudulent advertisements, malicious links, \u201cAvurudu offers\u201d and giveaways, fake trading platforms, counterfeit bank promotions, fake banking websites and application updates, QR code fraud, phishing emails, SMS phishing, imitation websites designed to appear legitimate, and caller ID spoofing.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      211.93,
      526.35,
      280.44
    ],
    "text": "Furthermore, perpetrators may misuse the images of high-ranking government officials, including the President and the Prime Minister, as well as celebrities, to create a false sense of trust among the public. There is also an increased risk of targeted phishing attacks, financial fraud, and identity theft through the misuse of sensitive personal data obtained via such deceptive practices.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      295.0,
      526.4,
      335.88
    ],
    "text": "Therefore, the Sri Lanka Police strongly urges the public to remain vigilant and exercise caution when conducting online transactions in order to avoid becoming victims of such fraudulent activities.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      350.44,
      186.41,
      363.72
    ],
    "text": "Police Media Division",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  }
]